Rating: 0
Thanks for all the suggestions as they were most helpful. When I saw how thick and sticky the batter was, I came back to the site to check out any reviews it see what people had to say because I thought I had a dud recipe on my hands. I'm very please with how these turned out. Here's what I did: added one egg white, 1/2 tsp. peppermint extract, and half of the crushed candy (yes, I had crushed mine finely too). I exchanged the sugar for Spenda abd I always use mini chocolate chips. Spooned it into a greased pan (no foil) and used a fork to spread it around. Topped it with the rest of the crushed candy (I used some candy canes that I've been saving for years!) Since I used a glass dish, I baked it at 350 deg. and for 2 minutes less than the recipe called for. Had to be careful in cutting them... after they were almost cooled down, I pressed my knife into the bars (don't drag the knife), and I just poked the knife blade around the sides to loosen. Let it finish cooling and gently lifted the small squares out of the pan. The crushed candy cane did not sink to the bottom and the sprinked candy on top looks very nice. Next time, I might double the batter (but not the choc. chips) to see how that works. They are addictive! It's a keeper.

Rating: 4
I've made three batches of this so far. They're divine -- so rich, chewy, chocolately and minty. The only change I made in the later batches was to nearly double the amount of peppermint candies, and to make sure that I hardly crushed them at all. The pic of this recipe -- I still have the issue of Gourmet it was in -- shows that all the peppermint drifts to the bottom of the cookie, so that was no surprise to me. My husband thinks these are some of the best cookies I've made!

Rating: 0
I got really tired of trying to crush the peppermint candies, so I only got about 1/2c and threw in 1/8 tsp of peppermint extract to boost the flavor a bit. I let them cook a little too long, but the center was still good, and I liked the flavor and the idea of it but it was really really chewy. I think the peppermints that I crushed were too fine, and as a result they all melted together at the bottom and made it so chewy. I would ditch the peppermints, stick with just peppermint extract, make it more of a brownie, and add some white chocolate chips for that nice contrast.

